isLocked Locked status for input attributes and non-tunable properties
 L = isLocked(OBJ) returns a logical value, L, which indicates whether
 \ \ \ input attributes and non - tunable properties are locked for the System
 \ \ \ object, OBJ. The object performs an internal initialization the first
 \ \ \ time the step method is executed. This initialization locks non-tunable
 \ \ \ properties and input specifications, such as dimensions, complexity, 
 \ \ \ and data type of the input data. After OBJ is locked, the isLocked method
 \ \ \ returns a true value.
 
 \ \ \ See also step, release.

release Allow property value and input characteristics changes
 \ \ \ release(OBJ) releases system resources (such as memory, file handles or
 \ \ \ hardware connections) of System object, OBJ. After release() is called, all the
 \ \ \ properties and input characteristics of OBJ can be changed.
 
 \ \ \ Once you call the release method on a System object, subsequent calls
 \ \ \ to setup, step, reset, or release are not supported for code
 \ \ \ generation.
 
 \ \ \ See also isLocked, step.

reset Reset the internal states of a System object
 \ \ \ reset(OBJ) resets the internal states of System object OBJ to their
 \ \ \ initial values.
 
 \ \ \ Objects that have internal states will describe in their help
 \ \ \ what the reset method does for that object. System objects
 \ \ \ with no states are unaffected by reset.
